President Trump welcomed the Crown Prince of Saudi Arabia and his representatives to the White House. Trump praised the strong relationship between the two countries and the promise of $400 billion in purchases from Saudi Arabia. He emphasized the quality of US military equipment and expressed hope that Saudi Arabia would provide jobs and investment to the US. The Crown Prince expressed his belief in the potential for further cooperation and mentioned preparations for the visit of his father, the King of Saudi Arabia. When asked about a school shooting in Maryland, Trump called it a terrible thing.